title: Jets splitting from Rodgers, wish him success
description: The Jets informed Aaron Rodgers that they will be moving in a different direction at the quarterback position, the team announced Thursday.
author: Rich Cimini

title: NBA scraps Curry-Ionescu shootout around ASG
description: The NBA says the 3-point shooting rematch between Stephen Curry and Sabrina Ionescu is not going to be part of the lineup for All-Star Weekend.

title: English football to use semi-automated offsides for first time
description: Semi-automated offside technology will be used in English domestic football for the first time during the fifth round of the FA Cup.

title: Littler wins Premier League night two in Glasgow
description: World champion Luke Littler defeats world number one Luke Humphries 6-5 in a last-leg decider to win night two of the Premier League in Glasgow.

title: Merson: Liverpool had two hands on title but Arsenal now have chance
description: Paul Merson says Liverpool had the Premier League title in two hands until James Tarkowski's incredible 98th-minute equaliser salvaged Everton a dramatic 2-2 draw in the last Merseyside derby at Goodison Park.

title: McLaren first team to reveal 2025 car as Norris drives at Silverstone
description: Reigning constructors' champions McLaren have become the first Formula 1 team to reveal their 2025 car ahead of the start of the new season.

title: Alex Bregman deal puts cherry on top of Boston's big offseason
description: A rocky winter for former Astros slugger Alex Bregman has finally reached its conclusion, and his winding journey through free agency is over.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: NIL Title IX ruling rescinded & Ohio State hires Matt Patricia | College Football Enquirer
